{
  "text": "A lumbar puncture was performed at baseline in all 36 participants of the cohort subset. All CSF samples included were collected in polypropylene tubes and centrifuged at 1000 g for 10 min at 4 C. The collected supernatant was aliquoted and stored at -80 C pending biochemical analysis. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . All CSF analyses were performed by board-certified laboratory technicians blinded to clinical information.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "24038752",
